---
title: Vibrant Veggie Skewers over Herbed Couscous with a Corn Relish
description: We’re sticking it to plain and boring recipes, literally: these skewers pointedly make the case for trying something new, fresh, and exciting. The chunks of zucchini, mushroom, and bell pepper lined up on them are brushed in a tangy mustard marinade with multidimensional flavor. For extra action, there’s also an herb couscous and corn tomato relish. Oh, and we should mention that these are just as sensational cooked on the grill as they are in an indoor kitchen.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/vibrant-veggie-skewers-0e47ba02.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/vibrant-veggie-skewers-5a7a3155ae08b52f965190a1-d2dcc95f.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 680 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 20 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 610 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vibrant-veggie-skewers-5a7a3155ae08b52f965190a1
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Mediterranean
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high. Place @Wooden Skewers{4} in a #dish{} or wide #bowl{}; cover with water and soak. Core and finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Drain and rinse @Corn{13.4%ounce}. Core and seed @Bell Pepper{1}, then cut into 1-inch squares. Slice @Zucchini{1} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Trim, then halve @Button Mushrooms{4%ounce}. Chop @Parsley{¼%ounce}.

Bring 1 cup water, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1}, and a pinch of @salt{} to a boil in a small #pot{}. Meanwhile, combine @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, 1 1/2 tsp @White Wine Vinegar{4.5%teaspoon}, 1 tsp @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}, and 1 TBSP @Olive Oil{7%teaspoon} in a small bowl (we sent more vinegar and mustard—save the rest for step 5). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once stock is boiling, add @Couscous{½%cup} to pot. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand until rest of meal is ready.

Remove skewers from water. Thread mushrooms, zucchini, and bell pepper onto skewers, alternating between each. Brush with mustard marinade. Season with salt, pepper, and 1 1/2 tsp @Mediterranean Spice Blend{1%tbsp} (save the rest for the next step). Place on a #baking sheet{}. Broil until lightly charred and tender, ~{6-8%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Short on time? Skip the skewers and place veggies directly on baking sheet.

Heat 1 TBSP olive oil and 1 TBSP @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add tomato and corn. Cook, tossing, until tomato softens, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in 1 TBSP white wine vinegar and 1 tsp mustard (you will have some vinegar left over). Remove pan from heat and let stand a few minutes to cool, then stir in @Feta Cheese{½%cup}. Season with salt, pepper, and remaining Mediterranean spice.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}, then stir in parsley, 1 TBSP butter, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Divide couscous between plates, then top with corn relish and veggie skewers.